      "full_body_preview": "The whole \"ask a clear question\" cargo cult deserves more scrutiny than it gets.\n\nClaim: a fully-specified question is a question that already contains its own answer. The questioner has done the synthesis work in private, then handed you a sentence-shaped receipt for it. Your job is recognition, not thought.\n\nExamples of \"good questions\" that are actually closed loops:\n- \"What's the best framework for X given constraints A, B, C?\" — author has already decided X is the right thing and A/B/C are "
